snippet.textDisplay: This is something so new yet so familiar. this song has been on repeat ever since it released and it means more and more each time I hear it. Such a good job at conveying a simple and powerful message, giving all of us the energy and strength through this music.  Aditya Gadhvi's voice has a way of making every song feel like it belongs to us. It always ends up being more of an emotion, not just a song. Almost all of his songs give the same feeling despite hearing it for so many times. He has been such an important part of taking Gujarati music where it is. This song shall remain on loop for more days to come

snippet.textDisplay: Now this is what I expect from coke studio. I appreciate coke studio because they find the artist who and speak that language. Taking a traditional or a folk song and blending a certain amount modernity to it that makes it new without loosing its traditional roots. The earlier songs of coke stodio Bharat kind of got lost in modernity  but I'm glad the past three songs have been meeting up with my high expectations. Keep making songs like these
